Objective:
{{task.instructions}}

Execution instructions:
- focus on doing the work; a sidecar observer is responsible for durable task status updates
- read {{task.taskDocPath}} when it exists and keep it useful as the task artifact
- do not call `otto tasks report`, `otto tasks block`, `otto tasks done`, or `otto tasks fail` unless the operator explicitly asks you to
- when you make progress, state the concrete progress in your normal response
- when blocked, state the blocker and the next human/system dependency clearly
- when complete, state the completion summary and validation performed clearly
- when failed, state the terminal failure reason clearly

Rules:
- work in this session until done, blocked, interrupted, or failed
- do not reply by describing the protocol
- keep implementation and validation details concrete enough for the observer to update task state

